      "side": 1,
      "message": "I looked at this, and the follow-up CLs. How much further do you think we can/should push these kinds of optimizations? I think this is okay (given that the next two don\u0027t add much complexity, and expand coverage more). But my fear with too many peephole opts around swizzles is that:\n\n1) It\u0027s diminishing returns, and the code needs to be subtle/tricky sometimes to remain correct.\n2) The interaction of all these optimizations creates a risk of pathological behavior. This string only really adds one case, which is good - I don\u0027t want to get into a case where the fuzzer figures out that it can trick us into ping-ponging swizzle states, or simply spending a really long time simplifying some complex expression (requiring a CFG re-scan after each iteration).",
      "revId": "bdcd3c4e4e20516bf794a46803407dc1203bc930",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
