      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027re absolutely right that this is diminishing returns. I ran it through DM with some breakpoints last night. I found that the `half4(1).rgb` simple case was hit fairly often (this was definitely the biggest bang for the buck, bar none). The complex path was only hit rarely, most often when executing randomly-generated FP trees. I\u0027m happy that this change improves codegen for complex zero-one swizzles, like `foo.x0y1`, but in practice we don\u0027t tend to leverage these much.\n\nI\u0027m done with this CL chain; I\u0027m not planning on going any further (not even sure what else could be done!). TBH my first swing at this task was straight to the end state--no chain of CLs, just one big ball of code--but it was just too large of a CL to reason about. It affected too many tests at once and it wasn\u0027t something I would have felt comfortable +1ing as a reviewer. I split it up specifically to keep review reasonable and so that the test files were changing in predictable ways at each iteration.",
